ABUJA (SundiataPost) – Lagos, Delta and Ebonyi states have topped the chart for new cases of COVID-19, according to an update released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Sunday night. In all there were 490 new cases out of which Lagos reported 118 new cases, followed by Delta State with 84 new cases.Ebonyi recorded 68 new COVID-19 infections. With the latest figures the total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria now stand at 24,567. The full report is as follows: 490 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-118Delta-84Ebonyi-68FCT-56Plateau-39Edo-29Katsina-21Imo-13Ondo-12Adamawa-11Osun-8Ogun-8Rivers-6Kano-5Enugu-3Bauchi-3Akwa Ibom-3Kogi-1Oyo-1Bayelsa-1 24,567 confirmed9,007 discharged565 deaths See the state by state breakdown below: By Joyce Remi- Babayeju ABUJA ( SundiataPost) – Nigeria has continued to record more cases of COVID-19 due to an increased number of Molecular Testing laboratories totaling 38  in the country. According to NCDC Molecular Laboratory Network on the NCDCgov handle the agency announced inclusion of four new laboratories bringing… June 17, 2020 In "Health" ABUJA (SundiataPost) - Four hundred and fifty-five Nigerians have died from COVID-19 complications. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) made this known in an update on Tuesday night on its Twitter handle @NCDCgov.It reported 490 new cases bringing the total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria to 17,148. The… June 17, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Lagos state recorded 148 COVID-19 patients on Sunday as a total of 313 new cases were confirmed by the Nigeria Centre for Disease control (NCDC). The Centre relased the report on Sunday on its official twitter handle thus: 313 new cases of #COVID19;… May 24, 2020 In "Top Stories"